just thought i  39 d give you some information about t shirt size prints  not sure at all how either company works  so keep that in mind  i have worked for a screen printing company for over 35 years  we use plastisol inks not water based inks  you have to have a screen for every color on your shirt  if it has 6 colors  then that is 6 screens  it takes time to set up all the screens and get them lined up with each other  the inks put in them and then print the shirts  if you have a dozen shirts say from size small to xxl  you will only get a design that is big enough to fit on the smallest size  that will go on all the shirts  they will not be 2  3 or 4 sizes  where i work we print small jobs and big jobs  we charge  20 per screen as a one time charge  six screens cost you  120 and you haven  39 t even bought a blank shirt  that doesn  39 t include printing cost either  after that it  39 s just shirt and printing cost  we usually will made two sets of screens  if the customer will pay  for say youth shirts   smaller size  and a bigger size for adults  however like i said the small adult through xxl will all get the same size adult design and you can only make it as big as will fit on the adult small shirt  hope this helps with how things are done  i have no idea how teesprings or printful work  and if you order 1 shirt at a time you can size it any way you want  however if you order say a dozen they may just size the art as big as they can for the smallest size so they can print them all at once with one set of screens
